    • Uses of GraphPath in org.jgrapht.graph

      Classes in org.jgrapht.graph that implement GraphPath 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  GraphPathImpl<V,E>
      Deprecated. 
      use GraphWalk instead
      class  GraphWalk<V,E>
      A walk in a graph is an alternating sequence of vertices and edges, starting and ending at a vertex, in which each edge is adjacent in the sequence to its two endpoints.
      class  SimpleGraphPath<V,E>
      Deprecated. 
      This class is ambiguous. Unlike the name or the description suggests, this class does NOT implement a Simple Path (a path in a graph without vertex repetition). Instead it implements a walk in a SimpleGraph. This functionality is now implemented by the class GraphWalk.
